article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- — JoVon McClanahan's 19 points helped Hawaii defeat CSU Bakersfield 78-67 on Thursday. McClanahan was 6 of 9 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 10 from the line for the Rainbow Warriors (9-5, 1-1 Big West Conference). Bernardo da Silva scored 18 points while going 6 of 6 and 6 of 10 from the free throw line, and added eight rebounds. Justin McKoy had 18 points and was 6 of 9 shooting, including 3 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 3 from the line. Dalph Panopio led the Roadrunners (5-9, 0-3) in scoring, finishing with 23 points. Corey Stephenson added 15 points and two steals for CSU Bakersfield. Kaleb Higgins also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
